[1] Malaysia (Terengganu)
Date: Sat 3 Jul 2004
From: ProMED <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: New Straits Times, 3 Jul 2004 [edited]
<http://www.emedia.com.my/Current_News/NST/Saturday/NewsBreak/20040703162015/A
rticle/indexb_html>

Dengue outbreak in Terengganu
------------------------------------
It was reported yesterday [Fri 2 Jul 2004] that 96 people were
hospitalized at the district hospital in Permaisuri, Setiu,
following a dengue outbreak there. Meanwhile, State Health director
Datuk Dr. Ahmad Razin Ahmad Maher said the situation in Kelantan was
under control, with a small number of cases reported so far.
Local councils have been directed to take immediate precautionary
measures against a dengue outbreak in the Setiu district of
Terengganu. State Public Administration, Local Government, Housing
and Health committee chairman Takiyuddin Hassan said a meeting with
the heads of all local authorities would be held tomorrow [Sun 4 Jul
2004] to discuss further measures. "We are not taking any chances.
Strict measures must be taken to rid the State from Aedes breeding
grounds."
Takiyuddin said it was unfortunate that many people did not take the
danger of dengue seriously. "They only react when there are cases in
their areas, but sometimes it is too late," he said.
[Byline: Mahsinah Syed Abdullah]
