[4] Bangladesh (Dhaka)
Date: 30 Jun 2004
From: ProMED <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Xinhua News Agency 30 Jun 2004 [edited]
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/>

114 infected with dengue this season in Bangladesh
-----------------------------------------------
The dengue control room in Dhaka reported 114 cases of dengue fever
this season [summer 2004] so far, with 62 of the patients still under
treatment, reported the New Age on Wed 30 Jun 2004.
Dhaka Mayor Sadeque Hossain Khoka said, on Tue 29 Jun 2004, that
mosquito control activities have been geared up by Dhaka City
Corporation (DCC) in recent weeks, adding that the dengue situation
in Dhaka is "totally under control." He added that city residents
need to be aware, and they should keep their own houses clean to stop
the spread of dengue fever.
State Minister for Labor and Employment Amanullah Aman also urged the
DCC to monitor dengue status, and stressed that commissioners of all
the 90 wards of Dhaka should come forward and report on the dengue
situation.
An awareness campaign in the media is expected to be launched soon to
make people aware of the deadly disease, according to sources with
the cleanliness and mosquito control advisory committee.
